The paper deals with unsupervised domain adaptation using deep learning and adversarial strategy, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed method involves a discriminative manifold learning framework, which is a technique used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a probabilistic discriminant criterion, which is a concept used in neural networks (cs.NE).
